  "prompt": "How many known viruses can infect humans?",
  "response": "As of the most recent estimates, there are **over 200 known viruses** that can infect humans. This number continues to grow as new viruses are discovered and more research is conducted. These viruses belong to various families, including:\n\n- **Herpesviridae** (e.g., herpes simplex virus, Epstein-Barr virus)\n- **Flaviviridae** (e.g., dengue virus, Zika virus, West Nile virus)\n- **Orthomyxoviridae** (e.g., influenza viruses)\n- **Coronaviridae** (e.g., SARS-CoV-2, which causes COVID-19)\n- **Retroviridae** (e.g., HIV)\n- **Paramyxoviridae** (e.g., measles virus, mumps virus)\n- **Picornaviridae** (e.g., rhinoviruses, which cause the common cold)\n- **Adenoviridae** (e.g., adenoviruses causing respiratory infections)\n\nIt's important to note that many viruses in the environment have yet to be identified or studied, and some may have the potential to jump from animals to humans in the future. Advances in virology and genomic sequencing are helping researchers better understand and catalog these pathogens.",
